Process Engineer

Novagard

- Cleveland, OH 44114 (Downtown area)

The Process Engineer is responsible for the optimization of manufacturing processes and equipment machinery within Novagard.
Essential Functions
Optimizes machinery to add automation and update equipment capabilities and performance.
Works closely with R&D function on scale up of new products
Dials in maintenance process to optimize PM’s.
Work with operations leaders to develop efficient, standardized work processes
Institute an Overall Equipment Effectiveness program.
Optimizes the manufacturing processes across 3 different divisions.
Assists in capital strategy to support organization.
Establish the process engineering function for the business.
Knowledge & Skills
In-depth knowledge of inventory control practices and systems. Ability to develop and document complex processes and controls.
Knowledge of chemical manufacturing processes.
Excellent problem-solving skills and the ability to effectively present information and analysis.
Skilled in Project Management to ensure timely delivery of results.
Advanced proficiency with Excel.
Ability to work in a complex, ambiguous environment.
Impeccable Math and statistical analysis
